In triangle $ABC,$ $a = 7,$ $b = 9,$ and $c = 4.$  Let $I$ be the incenter.

[asy]
unitsize(0.8 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, I;

B = (0,0);
C = (7,0);
A = intersectionpoint(arc(B,4,0,180),arc(C,9,0,180));
I = incenter(A,B,C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(incircle(A,B,C));

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
dot("$I$", I, NE);
[/asy]

Then
\[\overrightarrow{I} = x \overrightarrow{A} + y \overrightarrow{B} + z \overrightarrow{C},\]where $x,$ $y,$ and $z$ are constants such that $x + y + z = 1.$  Enter the ordered triple $(x,y,z).$

ground_truth_answer:
\text{Solution set} =
\begin{cases}
\{x \mid x < a \text{ or } x > 1\}, & \text{when } a < 1 \\
\{x \mid x \neq 1\}, & \text{when } a = 1 \\
\{x \mid x < 1 \text{ or } x > a\}, & \text{when } a > 1
\end{cases}

problem:
Mark loves to see shows in theaters. He decided to visit the theater at least once a week for 6 weeks. The duration of the performances and the price of the tickets vary each week: 

- Week 1: 3-hour performance, $5 per hour;
- Week 2: 2.5-hour performance, $6 per hour;
- Week 3: 4-hour performance, $4 per hour;
- Week 4: 3-hour performance, $5 per hour;
- Week 5: 3.5-hour performance, $6 per hour;
- Week 6: 2-hour performance, $7 per hour.

There is a special discount rate that changes for different weeks:
- Weeks 1 and 4: the discount is 20%;
- Weeks 2 and 5: the discount is 10%;
- Weeks 3 and 6: there is no discount.

Additionally, Mark has to pay $3 in transportation costs for each visit to the theater. He also decided to attend two shows during week 5. Calculate the spending of Mark on visits to the theater, including ticket and transportation costs, in 6 weeks.

